# virtual-store-dir was set here to work around Windows 260-char MAX_PATH in Android
# Gradle/CMake builds, but it breaks Metro module resolution. The APK is built and
# installed separately when this setting is active; revert afterwards for normal dev.
# virtual-store-dir=E:\pnpm-store

# Feature 005 (Expo SDK 56 upgrade) NOTE: tried virtual-store-dir-max-length=40 to
# shorten node_modules/.pnpm/<pkg>@<ver>_<hash>/ dir names and fix the Android CMake
# CMAKE_OBJECT_PATH_MAX (250) overflow on react-native-worklets/-screens C++ builds.
# RESULT: it only trimmed the object DIR 221->201, but CMake replicates the FULL absolute
# source path under the object dir, so the worst object path was still 381 chars — AND
# the shortened store names broke jest/Metro module resolution (all 67 suites failed to
# load), same class of breakage as the relocated-store note above. REVERTED. The reliable
# fix is a short BUILD ROOT (the repo prefix appears ~twice in the object path); see
# specs/005-expo-sdk-56-upgrade/tasks.md T024.
